\begin{theorem}
Let $z_1$ and $z_2$ be complex numbers such that $z_2 \neq 0$. If $\cmod z$ denotes the modulus of a complex number $z$, then the modulus of their quotient is equal to the quotient of their moduli:
$$ \cmod {\frac {z_1} {z_2} } = \frac {\cmod {z_1} } {\cmod {z_2} } $$
\end{theorem}

